mform_help_subheadline_1 = MForm â€“ Redaxo AddOn for module-input-forms
mform_help_infotext_1 = MForm is a Redaxo add-on that makes the creation of module forms much easier. MForm uses templates which allow the administrator to customize the module style. MForm provides all the essential module input form elements for easy to integration.
mform_help_infotext_2 = For the validation of module forms, MForm uses the jQuery Validator Parsley which offers the possibility to assign standard validations to every possible input field.
mform_help_infotext_3 = MForm can be used in a similar way to the "rex_form" class. You can add form elements using different methods of an instance, and assign attributes, parameters, or options to them using other methods. However, in the design of MForm, the element methods were created in such a way that their constructors each process all possible attributes, parameters and options as a transfer array, whereby an element can be called "one-line" and can be created with little effort.

